id: pmc-99tc
title: Batch git tag timestamp lookup for full-history changelog
description: Gemini review on pm-cli#62 flagged that pm-changelog full-history generation shells out once per release tag to resolve timestamps. Track and fix this in pm-changelog by using one formatted git tag lookup for all matching release tags.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: changelog,performance,review
created_at: "2026-05-24T16:04:37.969Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T20:04:50.991Z"
author: codex-pm-changelog-review
release: v2026.05.24-14
resolution: "Replaced per-tag git log timestamp resolution with one formatted git tag listing that returns tag names and peeled/direct commit dates, preserving commit-date release windows for annotated and lightweight tags."
expected_result: Full-history changelog release tag discovery resolves tag names and commit timestamps with a bounded git process count instead of spawning once per tag.
actual_result: "Full-history release tag discovery now uses one git tag --list --format call for matching tags, parses timestamps in process, and passes regression coverage for annotated tag commit dates."
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-24T16:06:44.726Z",codex-pm-changelog-review,"Evidence: GitHub issue unbraind/pm-changelog#11 filed from Gemini review on pm-cli#62. Implemented package-side batch tag timestamp lookup with one formatted git tag command and a regression test that annotated tags use the target commit timestamp, not tagger date."
